article.headline: Oral Roberts 91, Centenary 67
article.story: SHREVEPORT, La. (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 23 points to lead Oral Roberts in a 91-67 rout of Centenary Thursday night. Fifteen of Green's points came on four fastbreak dunks and seven free throws. Chris Riouse added 21 points for the Golden Eagles (17-5, 8-2 Mid-Continent) and Ken Tutt, who was a perfect 6-of-6 from the free-throw line, added 17. Mickey Michalec finished with 10. Chad Maclies led the Gents (2-18, 0-9) with 25 points and 11 rebounds for his sixth double-double of the season. Jarmorrow Moragne added 19 and was a perfect 10-of-10 from the free-throw line. David Tolefree had 11. After a pair of free throws from Moragne, Maclies' tip-in brought the score within eight at 47-39 in the opening minutes of the second half. With a 12-point advantage, the Golden Eagles put the game out of reach with a 10-0 run over two minutes that put Oral Roberts up by 22 points.
